    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "283d737a_c536b96d",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph.js",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 20,
      "author": {
        "id": 12084
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-27T16:01:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we eagerly convert the array to rects we\u0027ll end up with a double-conversion, first this, and another one on the Flutter side to convert to TextBox. That could be avoided if this returned the floatArray as is.\n\nAlternatively, we could treat `_getRectsForPlaceholders` as public stable API and have Flutter call that instead.",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "34cd97da_8e276542",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph.js",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 20,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-31T14:57:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "With https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/312491 I\u0027m changing how SkRects are represented in CanvasKit to be float arrays.\n\nI\u0027m ok introducing a \"type\" called TextRects which is 4 floats representing the corners and then a float representing the direction. This means we can just return the flat Float32Array from getRectsForPlaceholders containing a multiple of 5 elements. This would avoid the double-conversion and be mostly compatible with plugging the rectangles into other APIs.",
      "parentUuid": "283d737a_c536b96d",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5d73ce85_656281cf",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph.js",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 88,
      "author": {
        "id": 9065
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-26T19:57:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "define fontStyle, strutStyle and placeholderStyle in CanvasKit like .CanvasKitParagraphStyle and CanvasKit.TextStyle\n\nusers wanting to make such styles and re-use them will need to call those methods.",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2c22102c_3126fd27",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph.js",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 88,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-31T14:57:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure about that - ParagraphStyle and TextStyle are defined that way because they are meant to be re-used by a developer in calls to APIs. fontStyle and strutStyle aren\u0027t used directly in an API call, right? As such, I wouldn\u0027t expect to need for a developer to hold onto those names.\n\nPlaceholderStyle, if it is commonly reused, could be exposed so the same object isn\u0027t created multiple times.",
      "parentUuid": "5d73ce85_656281cf",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ee360a05_d4fceb43",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph.js",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 107,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-31T14:57:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think this needs to be a SimpleType. These are just 5 numeric values, so I think it will be simpler/faster to just have _addPlaceHolder (in the bindings) take 5 floats as parameters. \n\nTaking it further, does addPlaceholder (in this file) need to take an object? If the goal is to make it so we handle default values gracefully, then I\u0027m fine as is, but would it be more ergonomic to take 5 parameters in order (width, height, offset, alignment, baseline) so the ones that are omitted more commonly are near the end and can be easily omitted to use the default value?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 107,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 107,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
