      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "13843286_08791595",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph_bindings.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 280,
      "author": {
        "id": 12084
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-27T16:01:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s a neat trick, but how do we know the compiler guarantees the exact layout of the `SimpleTextBox` struct? For example, what happens when we switch to 64-bit wasm?",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3e7b01e8_02e52be9",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph_bindings.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 280,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-31T14:57:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As the original author of this code (het@ is refactoring it), I was under the impression that C++ guarantees that the members of struct appear in memory in the same order as they are declared.\n\nI would not expect 64bit WASM (which seems a long way off) to change this, unless you are referring to alignment changes.",
      "parentUuid": "13843286_08791595",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "80445363_7d0c6cd9",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph_bindings.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 280,
      "author": {
        "id": 12084
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-31T16:18:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, alignment is the risky one. SimpleTextBox is a 5*32-bit struct, which means it may not align exactly in 64-bit world (i.e. the compiler may choose to make it a 6*32-bit struct).",
      "parentUuid": "3e7b01e8_02e52be9",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "499b2057_9b057612",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph_bindings.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 355,
      "author": {
        "id": 9065
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-26T19:57:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What is a placeholder in this context? what is it\u0027s purpose?",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "293e6a16_1dd4c771",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/paragraph_bindings.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 355,
      "author": {
        "id": 10154
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-29T23:15:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is a signal to the paragraph builder that some non-text content is going to be inlined into the paragraph. For example, this is used in Flutter to place widgets in text.",
      "parentUuid": "499b2057_9b057612",
      "revId": "abbae2511d55085dfc1455ddc225a4ef2d1c97d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
